<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-15-0279 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper, updating the findings of an earlier study, provides additionalevidence that sheet metal workers in the construction trades are at increasedrisk for asbestos-related disease. A proportional analysis of cause ofdeath among 331 New York sheet metal workers found a significantly elevatedPMR for lung cancer (PMR = 186). In addition, there were six deaths attributableto mesothelioma (three classified as lung cancer deaths) and three deathcertificates mentioned asbestosis or pulmonary fibrosis, although noneof these three deaths were attributed to these diseases.</TEXT></DOC>